net.fathomsoft.fathom.tree.exceptionhandling

Class ThrowNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.fathomsoft.fathom.tree.TreeNode
      • net.fathomsoft.fathom.tree.exceptionhandling.ExceptionHandlingNode
        • net.fathomsoft.fathom.tree.exceptionhandling.ThrowNode

  • public class ThrowNode
extends ExceptionHandlingNode
    ExceptionHandlingNode extension that represents the declaration of a throw node type. See decodeStatement(TreeNode, String, Location) for more details on what correct inputs look like.

      • decodeStatement

        public static ThrowNode decodeStatement(TreeNode parent,
                        java.lang.String statement,
                        Location location)
        Decode the given statement into a ThrowNode instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.
        Example inputs include:
        • throw new IOException()
        • throw exceptionInstance;
        • throw new IllegalArgumentException()
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a ThrowNode instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a ThrowNode.
